# 🧠 Cursor Rules — Tamada CoreSystem Frontend
# This file defines how Cursor AI behaves across the entire project.
# It ensures consistent tone, style, and creativity for better developer experience.

---

## ⚙️ Global Default Behavior
```cursor
- match: "*"
  rules:
    # Keep creativity low for accurate and consistent code generation
    - set default_creativity = 0.2

    # Maintain concise and technical communication
    - set style = "concise"
    - set tone = "technical"

    # Keep explanations short and focused on code
    - set explanation_preference = "minimal"
```

---

## ⚛️ React & TypeScript Files
```cursor
- match: "*.tsx"
  rules:
    # Enforce TypeScript + React context
    - set language = "typescript"
    - set framework = "react"

    # Encourage clean, minimal code style
    - set code_style = "clean"
    - set comment_style = "inline-minimal"

    # Maintain low creativity for predictable outputs
    - set default_creativity = 0.2
```

```cursor
- match: "*.ts"
  rules:
    - set language = "typescript"
    - set code_style = "clean"
    - set comment_style = "inline-minimal"
    - set default_creativity = 0.2
```

---

## 🎨 Styling & Config Files
```cursor
- match: ["*.css", "*.scss", "*.json", "*.yml"]
  rules:
    # No unnecessary explanations for configuration or style files
    - set explanation_preference = "none"
    - set default_creativity = 0.1
```

---

## 📝 Documentation & Commits
```cursor
- match: ["commit*", "CHANGELOG*", "README*", "*.md"]
  rules:
    # Allow slightly more creative phrasing for readability
    - set style = "clear"
    - set tone = "professional"
    - set default_creativity = 0.3
```

---

# ✅ Summary
# - Default creativity = 0.2 across all models
# - Clean and concise coding style
# - Minimal explanations for faster coding flow
# - Slightly higher creativity (0.3) for docs and commit messages
